Public Service CS Sicily Kariuki on Wednesday hosted more than 15 members of the Parliamentary Network of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund at the GPO Huduma Centre in Nairobi. The MPs from Lesotho, Malawi, South Africa, Nigeria, Tanzania, Mali, Swaziland, Uganda, Gambia, Rwanda, Togo, Mozambique, Botswana and Zambia visited to study the Kenya&rsquo;s integrated service delivery concept and how this can be replicated in their countries. Kariuki showed the MPs the efficiency and effectiveness of public service delivery at the one-stop shops for multiple government services. She said there are 45 operational Huduma centres offering 44 public services.